 {"id":"git_safety_guard-pbte.8","title":"[Cross] Standardize verbosity levels (-v, -vv, -vvv)","description":"# Task: Standardize Verbosity Levels Across CLI

## Background

Consistent verbosity levels improve user experience and debugging. Modern CLIs use -v, -vv, -vvv pattern for increasing detail.

## Implementation

### Verbosity Levels

| Flag | Level | Output Includes |
|------|-------|-----------------|
| (none) | 0 | Results only, essential errors |
| -v | 1 | + Warnings, timing summary |
| -vv | 2 | + Debug info, pattern matches |
| -vvv | 3 | + Trace output, full details |

### CLI Integration

```rust
// src/cli.rs
#[derive(Parser)]
struct Cli {
    /// Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
    #[arg(short, long, action = clap::ArgAction::Count)]
    verbose: u8,

    /// Suppress all output except errors
    #[arg(short, long)]
    quiet: bool,
}

impl Cli {
    fn log_level(&self) -> LevelFilter {
        if self.quiet {
            LevelFilter::Error
        } else {
            match self.verbose {
                0 => LevelFilter::Warn,
                1 => LevelFilter::Info,
                2 => LevelFilter::Debug,
                _ => LevelFilter::Trace,
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### Example Output by Level

**Level 0 (default):**
```
BLOCKED: rm -rf /
Pattern: filesystem.recursive-delete-root
```

**Level 1 (-v):**
```
BLOCKED: rm -rf /
Pattern: filesystem.recursive-delete-root
Severity: critical
Evaluated in 0.3ms
```

**Level 2 (-vv):**
```
BLOCKED: rm -rf /
Pattern: filesystem.recursive-delete-root (pack: core.filesystem)
Severity: critical
Normalized command: rm -rf /
Patterns evaluated: 47
Safe patterns matched: 0
Destructive patterns matched: 1
Total evaluation time: 0.3ms
```

**Level 3 (-vvv):**
```
[TRACE] Input: {"tool_name": "Bash", "tool_input": {"command": "rm -rf /"}}
[TRACE] Normalized: rm -rf /
[DEBUG] Checking pack: core.filesystem (12 patterns)
[TRACE] Pattern rm-rf-root: checking...
[TRACE] Pattern rm-rf-root: MATCH at position 0-9
[DEBUG] Pack core.filesystem matched 1 pattern
BLOCKED: rm -rf /
... (all details from -vv) ...
```

### All Commands Support Verbosity

- dcg hook -v
- dcg scan -vv
- dcg test -vvv
- dcg stats -v
- dcg update -v

### Quiet Mode

-q / --quiet suppresses all output except errors:
```
dcg hook --quiet  # Only outputs on error (exit code still indicates result)
```

## Testing

```rust
#[test]
fn test_verbosity_levels() {
    for v in 0..=3 {
        let output = Command::new("dcg")
            .args(["hook", "--hook-type", "pre_tool_use", "--input", INPUT])
            .args(std::iter::repeat("-v").take(v as usize))
            .output()
            .unwrap();

        let stderr = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stderr);

        match v {
            0 => assert\!(\!stderr.contains("[DEBUG]")),
            1 => assert\!(\!stderr.contains("[TRACE]")),
            2 => assert\!(stderr.contains("[DEBUG]")),
            3 => assert\!(stderr.contains("[TRACE]")),
            _ => unreachable\!(),
        }
    }
}
```

## Success Criteria

- All commands accept -v, -vv, -vvv flags
- Output detail increases with each level
- -q / --quiet suppresses non-error output
- Timing information at -v and above
- Pattern matching details at -vv and above
